info.title: Selling Partner API for Reports
info.description: The Selling Partner API for Reports lets you retrieve and manage a variety of reports that can help selling partners manage their businesses.

get.description:
Returns report details for the reports that match the filters that you specify.

**Usage Plan:**

| Rate (requests per second) | Burst |
| ---- | ---- |
| 0.0222 | 10 |

The `x-amzn-RateLimit-Limit` response header returns the usage plan rate limits that were applied to the requested operation, when available. The table above indicates the default rate and burst values for this operation. Selling partners whose business demands require higher throughput may see higher rate and burst values than those shown here. For more information, refer to [Usage Plans and Rate Limits in the Selling Partner API](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/usage-plans-and-rate-limits-in-the-sp-api).

parameters.name: reportTypes
parameters.description: A list of report types used to filter reports. Refer to [Report Type Values](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/report-type-values) for more information. When reportTypes is provided, the other filter parameters (processingStatuses, marketplaceIds, createdSince, createdUntil) and pageSize may also be provided. Either reportTypes or nextToken is required.

parameters.name: processingStatuses
parameters.description: A list of processing statuses used to filter reports.

x-docgen-enum-table-extension.description: The report was cancelled. There are two ways a report can be cancelled: an explicit cancellation request before the report starts processing, or an automatic cancellation if there is no data to return.
The report was aborted due to a fatal error.
The report has not yet started processing. It may be waiting for another `IN_PROGRESS` report.

parameters.name: marketplaceIds
parameters.description: A list of marketplace identifiers used to filter reports. The reports returned will match at least one of the marketplaces that you specify.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The maximum number of reports to return in a single call.

parameters.name: createdSince
parameters.description: The earliest report creation date and time for reports to include in the response, in ISO 8601 date time format. The default is 90 days ago. Reports are retained for a maximum of 90 days.

parameters.name: createdUntil
parameters.description: The latest report creation date and time for reports to include in the response, in ISO 8601 date time format. The default is now.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: A string token returned in the response to your previous request. `nextToken` is returned when the number of results exceeds the specified `pageSize` value. To get the next page of results, call the `getReports` operation and include this token as the only parameter. Specifying `nextToken` with any other parameters will cause the request to fail.
